  </div>

  <!-- 2. IDS vs IPS -->
  <div class="d42-infographic">
    <div class="d42-infographic-title">IDS / IPS â€” Inline vs Promiscuous (SPAN) Port</div>
    <svg viewBox="0 0 720 250" style="width:100%;height:auto;display:block;font-family:'Sora',sans-serif;">
      <defs><marker id="idA" markerWidth="9" markerHeight="9" refX="7" refY="3" orient="auto"><path d="M0,0 L7,3 L0,6 Z" fill="#8a8a8a"/></marker>
      <marker id="idR" markerWidth="9" markerHeight="9" refX="7" refY="3" orient="auto"><path d="M0,0 L7,3 L0,6 Z" fill="#d31324"/></marker></defs>
      <text x="14" y="32" fill="#ff8a93" font-size="11" font-weight="700">Inline â€” IPS (preventative)</text>
      <g font-size="10" text-anchor="middle">
        <rect x="40" y="44" width="110" height="34" rx="5" fill="#1c1c1c" stroke="#7a7a7a"/><text x="95" y="65" fill="#e6e6e6">Traffic</text>
        <rect x="250" y="44" width="170" height="34" rx="5" fill="#2a0d10" stroke="#d31324"/><text x="335" y="60" fill="#f5f5f5">IPS â€” in the path</text><text x="335" y="72" fill="#ffb3bb" font-size="8">inspects &amp; blocks</text>
        <rect x="520" y="44" width="110" height="34" rx="5" fill="#1c1c1c" stroke="#7a7a7a"/><text x="575" y="65" fill="#e6e6e6">Destination</text>
      </g>
      <g stroke="#8a8a8a" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#idA)"><line x1="150" y1="61" x2="248" y2="61"/><line x1="420" y1="61" x2="518" y2="61"/></g>
      <text x="40" y="98" fill="#3fb950" font-size="9">âœ“ Drops malicious packets in real time.</text>
      <text x="360" y="98" fill="#d8a23a" font-size="9">âš  Fail-closed = full outage (single point of failure).</text>

      <line x1="14" y1="118" x2="706" y2="118" stroke="rgba(255,255,255,0.08)"/>

      <text x="14" y="146" fill="#ff8a93" font-size="11" font-weight="700">SPAN / TAP â€” IDS (detective)</text>
      <g font-size="10" text-anchor="middle">
        <rect x="40" y="158" width="110" height="34" rx="5" fill="#1c1c1c" stroke="#7a7a7a"/><text x="95" y="179" fill="#e6e6e6">Traffic</text>
        <rect x="250" y="158" width="120" height="34" rx="5" fill="#262626" stroke="#7a7a7a"/><text x="310" y="179" fill="#e6e6e6">Switch</text>
        <rect x="470" y="158" width="110" height="34" rx="5" fill="#1c1c1c" stroke="#7a7a7a"/><text x="525" y="179" fill="#e6e6e6">Destination</text>
        <rect x="250" y="212" width="120" height="30" rx="5" fill="#2a0d10" stroke="#d31324"/><text x="310" y="231" fill="#f5f5f5">IDS â€” copy only</text>
      </g>
      <g stroke="#8a8a8a" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#idA)"><line x1="150" y1="175" x2="248" y2="175"/><line x1="370" y1="175" x2="468" y2="175"/></g>
      <line x1="310" y1="192" x2="310" y2="210" stroke="#d31324" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="3 2" marker-end="url(#idR)"/>
      <text x="384" y="226" fill="#d8a23a" font-size="9" text-anchor="start">âš  Detects &amp; alerts only â€” cannot block.</text>
      <text x="384" y="240" fill="#3fb950" font-size="9" text-anchor="start">âœ“ A sensor failure does not disrupt traffic.</text>
    </svg>
  </div>

  <!-- 3. IPSec AH vs ESP -->
  <div class="d42-infographic">
    <div class="d42-infographic-title">IPSec â€” AH vs ESP Packet Structure</div>
    <svg viewBox="0 0 720 250" style="width:100%;height:auto;display:block;font-family:'Sora',sans-serif;">
      <text x="14" y="30" fill="#ff8a93" font-size="11" font-weight="700">AH â€” Authentication Header (Protocol 51)</text>
      <g font-size="9.5" text-anchor="middle">
        <rect x="60" y="52" width="170" height="36" fill="#2a2a2a" stroke="#7a7a7a"/><text x="145" y="68" fill="#f5f5f5">Original IP Header</text><text x="145" y="80" fill="#9aa3c7" font-size="8">authenticated</text>
        <rect x="230" y="52" width="150" height="36" fill="#2a0d10" stroke="#d31324"/><text x="305" y="68" fill="#f5f5f5">AH Header</text><text x="305" y="80" fill="#9aa3c7" font-size="8">HMAC integrity</text>
        <rect x="380" y="52" width="280" height="36" fill="#1c1c1c" stroke="#7a7a7a"/><text x="520" y="68" fill="#f5f5f5">Payload / Data</text><text x="520" y="80" fill="#ff8a93" font-size="8">NOT encrypted âœ—</text>
      </g>
      <line x1="60" y1="44" x2="660" y2="44" stroke="#3fb950" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="360" y="40" fill="#3fb950" font-size="8.5" text-anchor="middle">â—€ authenticated â€” the ENTIRE packet, including the IP header â–¶</text>
      <text x="60" y="106" fill="#d8a23a" font-size="9">âš  Because the IP header is authenticated, AH breaks NAT (NAT rewrites that header).</text>

      <line x1="14" y1="124" x2="706" y2="124" stroke="rgba(255,255,255,0.08)"/>

      <text x="14" y="150" fill="#ff8a93" font-size="11" font-weight="700">ESP â€” Encapsulating Security Payload (Protocol 50)</text>
      <g font-size="9" text-anchor="middle">
        <rect x="40" y="178" width="120" height="36" fill="#2a2a2a" stroke="#7a7a7a"/><text x="100" y="194" fill="#f5f5f5">New IP Header</text><text x="100" y="206" fill="#9aa3c7" font-size="8">not protected</text>
        <rect x="160" y="178" width="110" height="36" fill="#2a0d10" stroke="#d31324"/><text x="215" y="194" fill="#f5f5f5">ESP Header</text><text x="215" y="206" fill="#9aa3c7" font-size="8">SPI + Seq#</text>
        <rect x="270" y="178" width="230" height="36" fill="rgba(211,19,36,0.3)" stroke="#d31324"/><text x="385" y="194" fill="#ffd2d5">Payload</text><text x="385" y="206" fill="#ffd2d5" font-size="8">AES encrypted âœ“</text>
        <rect x="500" y="178" width="90" height="36" fill="#2a2a2a" stroke="#7a7a7a"/><text x="545" y="199" fill="#f5f5f5">ESP Trailer</text>
        <rect x="590" y="178" width="90" height="36" fill="#2a0d10" stroke="#d31324"/><text x="635" y="194" fill="#f5f5f5">ESP Auth</text><text x="635" y="206" fill="#9aa3c7" font-size="8">tag</text>
      </g>
      <line x1="270" y1="170" x2="500" y2="170" stroke="#ff8a93" stroke-width="1"/><text x="385" y="166" fill="#ff8a93" font-size="8" text-anchor="middle">â—€ encrypted â–¶</text>
      <line x1="160" y1="222" x2="680" y2="222" stroke="#3fb950" stroke-width="1"/><text x="420" y="234" fill="#3fb950" font-size="8" text-anchor="middle">â—€ authenticated (ESP header â†’ trailer) â–¶ Â· headers stay clear, so ESP is NAT-compatible âœ“</text>
    </svg>
  </div>

  <!-- 4. 802.1X EAP flow -->
  <div class="d42-infographic">
    <div class="d42-infographic-title">802.1X â€” EAP Authentication Flow</div>
    <svg viewBox="0 0 720 300" style="width:100%;height:auto;display:block;font-family:'Sora',sans-serif;">
      <defs><marker id="eA" markerWidth="9" markerHeight="9" refX="7" refY="3" orient="auto"><path d="M0,0 L7,3 L0,6 Z" fill="#d31324"/></marker></defs>
      <g text-anchor="middle">
        <rect x="60" y="20" width="160" height="40" rx="6" fill="#1c1c1c" stroke="#7a7a7a"/><text x="140" y="40" fill="#f5f5f5" font-size="10" font-weight="700">Supplicant</text><text x="140" y="53" fill="#9aa3c7" font-size="8">device / laptop</text>
        <rect x="280" y="20" width="160" height="40" rx="6" fill="#2a0d10" stroke="#d31324"/><text x="360" y="40" fill="#f5f5f5" font-size="10" font-weight="700">Authenticator</text><text x="360" y="53" fill="#9aa3c7" font-size="8">switch / WAP Â· port blocked</text>
        <rect x="500" y="20" width="160" height="40" rx="6" fill="#1c1c1c" stroke="#7a7a7a"/><text x="580" y="40" fill="#f5f5f5" font-size="10" font-weight="700">Auth Server</text><text x="580" y="53" fill="#9aa3c7" font-size="8">RADIUS / TACACS+</text>
      </g>
      <g stroke="#3a3a3a" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="3 3"><line x1="140" y1="60" x2="140" y2="252"/><line x1="360" y1="60" x2="360" y2="252"/><line x1="580" y1="60" x2="580" y2="252"/></g>
      <g font-size="9" fill="#e6e6e6">
        <text x="250" y="80" text-anchor="middle">â‘  EAP-Start / Identity Request</text>
        <line x1="140" y1="86" x2="358" y2="86" stroke="#d31324" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#eA)"/>
        <text x="470" y="108" text-anchor="middle">â‘¡ RADIUS Access-Request</text>
        <line x1="360" y1="114" x2="578" y2="114" stroke="#d31324" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#eA)"/>
        <text x="470" y="136" text-anchor="middle">â‘¢ EAP Challenge</text>
        <line x1="580" y1="142" x2="362" y2="142" stroke="#d31324" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#eA)"/>
        <text x="250" y="164" text-anchor="middle">â‘£ Challenge forwarded</text>
        <line x1="360" y1="170" x2="142" y2="170" stroke="#d31324" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#eA)"/>
        <text x="250" y="192" text-anchor="middle">â‘¤ EAP Response (credentials / cert)</text>
        <line x1="140" y1="198" x2="358" y2="198" stroke="#d31324" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#eA)"/>
        <line x1="360" y1="216" x2="578" y2="216" stroke="#d31324" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#eA)"/>
        <text x="470" y="212" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#9aa3c7">forwarded to server</text>
        <text x="470" y="238" text-anchor="middle">â‘¥ RADIUS Access-Accept</text>
        <line x1="580" y1="244" x2="362" y2="244" stroke="#3fb950" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#eA)"/>
      </g>
      <rect x="240" y="262" width="240" height="26" rx="6" fill="rgba(63,185,80,0.14)" stroke="#3fb950"/><text x="360" y="279" fill="#9fe6ab" font-size="9.5" text-anchor="middle">Port OPENED â€” network access granted âœ“</text>
    </svg>
  </div>
        </div>
        <!-- closes d42-infographics-row -->
      </div>
      <!-- closes d42-diagram panel -->

      </section>

      <!-- 4.3 â€” Implement Secure Communication Channels -->
      <section class="section cissp-notes" data-reveal>
        <div class="section-head">
          <p class="section-label">4.3 &mdash; Implement Secure Communication Channels</p>
          <h2 class="section-title">Secure communication channels.</h2>
          <p class="section-copy">
            Implementing secure communication channels by design &mdash; voice and video,
            remote access, data communications, and third-party connectivity. Hover any box for
            the detail and an example.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="note-panel" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <h3 class="note-subtitle">Exam essentials</h3>
          <ul class="note-list">
            <li><strong>Voice:</strong> VoIP is packet-switched and latency-sensitive &mdash; prioritize it with QoS. SIP signals on port 5060 (MD5 integrity); SRTP encrypts the media. Secure VoIP = separate VLAN + VoIP-aware firewall + strong authentication.</li>
            <li><strong>Email:</strong> S/MIME SIGNED = integrity + non-repudiation; ENVELOPED = + confidentiality (CA-based, enterprise). PGP = decentralized web of trust (personal/office).</li>
            <li><strong>VPN:</strong> PPTP is legacy/weak (RC4 via MPPE, IP-only); L2TP alone has NO encryption &mdash; pair it with IPSec; SSL VPN is browser-based (no client). Split tunnel = HIGH RISK; full tunnel forces all traffic through corporate security.</li>
            <li><strong>IPSec:</strong> AH authenticates the whole packet but BREAKS NAT; ESP encrypts the payload and is NAT-compatible. Transport mode = payload only (host-to-host); tunnel mode = whole packet (site-to-site). IKE = ISAKMP + Diffie-Hellman.</li>
            <li><strong>AAA:</strong> RADIUS = UDP, encrypts only the password, combines auth + authz; <strong>TACACS+</strong> = TCP, encrypts everything, separates AAA &mdash; the most robust; Diameter = RADIUS successor (encrypts username + password, uses IPSec).</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div id="domain43-container" class="osi-container"></div>
      </section>

      
    </main>

